cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.IR 

This paper deals with transfer learning for endoscopic image classification, which involves computer vision (CV) techniques such as feature extraction and classification. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also proposes a method for regularization using L2 distance constraints, which falls under the category of machine learning (ML) and specifically, supervised learning. Hence, cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) are also likely sub-categories. Additionally, the paper deals with medical imaging, which is a sub-field of multimedia (MM) and information retrieval (IR). Therefore, cs.MM and cs.IR are also possible sub-categories.
